This paper discusses the privacy concerns related to biometric authentication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on voice-based authentication for mobile devices, which could also fall under the categories of mobile computing (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing protocols, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of the proposed protocol, which could fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CY).
